{"title_page": "Isabelle (Animal Crossing)", "text_new": "{{short description|Fictional character from the Animal Crossing franchise}}\n{{italic title|noerror|string=Animal Crossing|all=yes}}\n{{Infobox character\n| color              = yellow\n| image              = File:Isabelle AF.png\n| caption            = Isabelle as featured in promotional art for ''[[Animal Crossing: New Horizons]]''\n| name               = Isabelle\n| series             = [[Animal Crossing]]\n| firstgame          = ''[[Animal Crossing: New Leaf]]'' (2012)\n| creator            = \n| voice              = \n| origin             = \n| nationality        = \n| family             = Digby (twin brother)\n| occupation         = Secretary\n| species = [[Dog]], [[Shih Tzu]]\n}}\n'''Isabelle''', known as {{nihongo|'''Shizue'''|\u3057\u305a\u3048}} in Japan, is a fictional character from the ''[[Animal Crossing]]'' series of video games. She is a kindly [[Shih Tzu]] that debuted in the 2012 release ''[[Animal Crossing: New Leaf]]'', where she serves as the secretary to the player character. Isabelle has received positive reception, to the point of becoming one of the most prominent characters in the ''Animal Crossing'' franchise and its ''de facto'' mascot. Her popularity has also led to appearances outside of the ''Animal Crossing'' series, including a playable role in the crossover fighting game ''[[Super Smash Bros. Ultimate]]''.\n\n==Concept and creation==\nIsabelle is a golden-coloured [[Shih Tzu]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/e3/2019/6/12/18662876/isabelle-animal-crossing-new-horizons-nintendo-switch-e3-2019-return|title=Hooray: Isabelle will be in Animal Crossing: New Horizons|last=Hernandez|first=Patricia|date=2019-06-12|website=Polygon|language=en|access-date=2019-12-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200101163840/https://www.polygon.com/e3/2019/6/12/18662876/isabelle-animal-crossing-new-horizons-nintendo-switch-e3-2019-return|archive-date=2020-01-01|url-status=live}}</ref> originally named Shizue in Japanese.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nintendojo.com/features/editorials/evaluating-localization-in-defense-of-noa-treehouse |title=Evaluating Localization: In Defense of NOA Treehouse |work=Nintendojo |last=Pelone |first=Anthony |date=April 6, 2016 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606092001/http://www.nintendojo.com/features/editorials/evaluating-localization-in-defense-of-noa-treehouse |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Animal Crossing'' designers wanted players to reject Isabelle's offer of a ceremony for various accomplishments as mayor at least once so that they feel bad about having done so.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://iwataasks.nintendo.com/interviews/#/3ds/animalcrossing-newleaf/0/1 |title=Nintendo 3DS |work=[[Nintendo]] |last=Iwata |first=Satoru |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190622234955/http://iwataasks.nintendo.com/interviews/#/3ds/animalcrossing-newleaf/0/1 |archive-date=June 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Animal Crossing'' director Katsuya Eguchi and ''New Leaf'' producer [[Aya Kyogoku]] both enjoyed Isabelle; Eguchi appreciated her for her smile, friendliness, and clumsiness.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2016/08/25/we-asked-splatoons-producers-to-pick-sides-in-splatfest |title=We Asked Splatoon\u2019s Producers to Pick Sides in Splatfest |work=[[IGN]] |date=August 25, 2016 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606064041/https://www.ign.com/articles/2016/08/25/we-asked-splatoons-producers-to-pick-sides-in-splatfest |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2467124/animal-crossing-favorite-characters/ |title='Animal Crossing' Developers Pick Their Favorite Characters |work=[[MTV]] |last=Cipriano |first=Jason |date=May 15, 2013 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606091956/http://www.mtv.com/news/2467124/animal-crossing-favorite-characters/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIsabelle's appearance in ''[[Super Smash Bros. Ultimate]]'' is based on fellow ''Animal Crossing'' character [[Villager (Animal Crossing)|Villager]]. However, ''Super Smash Bros.'' series director [[Masahiro Sakurai]] chose not to make Isabelle an \"Echo Fighter\" (a character with relatively minor differences from another) of Villager because of her different animations and her proportions being based on character models in ''[[Animal Crossing: New Leaf]]'', as opposed to earlier ''Animal Crossing'' character models.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.siliconera.com/2018/09/29/sakurai-talks-about-why-isabelle-isnt-an-echo-fighter-and-the-chaos-that-is-smash-bros/ |title=Sakurai Talks About Why Isabelle Isn\u2019t An Echo Fighter, And The Chaos That Is Smash Bros. |work=[[Siliconera]] |last=Wong |first=Alistair |date=September 29, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606071437/https://www.siliconera.com/2018/09/29/sakurai-talks-about-why-isabelle-isnt-an-echo-fighter-and-the-chaos-that-is-smash-bros/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Appearances==\nIsabelle first appeared in the 2012 video game ''[[Animal Crossing: New Leaf]]'' along with her twin brother [[Digby (Animal Crossing)|Digby]]. In the game, she acts as the secretary to the player character, who becomes the town mayor, and assists them with various tasks. She has appeared in several ''Animal Crossing'' games since, including ''[[Animal Crossing: Happy Home Designer]]'', ''[[Animal Crossing: amiibo Festival]]'', ''[[Animal Crossing: Pocket Camp]] and [[Animal Crossing: New Horizons]].''\n\nOutside of the ''Animal Crossing'' franchise, Isabelle has also appeared in the ''[[Super Smash Bros.]]'' series, first appearing as an assist trophy in ''[[Super Smash Bros. for Nintendo 3DS and Wii U]]'' before becoming a playable fighter in the [[Nintendo Switch]] sequel ''[[Super Smash Bros. Ultimate]]''. Isabelle also appears in the [[Wii U]] video game ''[[Mario Kart 8]]'' as a downloadable racer, as well as in its Nintendo Switch port ''[[Mario Kart 8 Deluxe]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2015/4/1/8328155/mario-kart-8-animal-crossing-dlc-release-date-price |title=Mario Kart 8's Animal Crossing DLC arrives early on April 23 |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |last=Sarkar |first=Samit |date=April 1, 2015 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322194837/https://www.polygon.com/2015/4/1/8328155/mario-kart-8-animal-crossing-dlc-release-date-price |archive-date=March 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Player costumes based on Isabelle appear in ''[[Super Mario Maker]]'' and ''[[Monster Hunter 4|Monster Hunter 4 Ultimate]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2015/6/5/8737331/monster-hunter-4-animal-crossing-devil-may-cry |title=Animal Crossing, Devil May Cry and more come to Monster Hunter 4 this month |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |last=McWhertor |first=Michael |date=June 5, 2015 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322194837/https://www.polygon.com/2015/6/5/8737331/monster-hunter-4-animal-crossing-devil-may-cry |archive-date=March 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Isabelle also appears as part of Nintendo's [[amiibo]] line of [[toys-to-life]] figures. She has 2 figures from the Animal Crossing line, 1 from the Smash Bros line, and several different Animal Crossing amiibo cards. \n\n===In other media===\nIsabelle appears in a one-off gag manga in the magazine ''[[CoroCoro]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://kotaku.com/animal-crossing-sure-looks-different-in-manga-form-1250063591 |title=Animal Crossing Sure Looks... Different in Manga Form |work=[[Kotaku]] |last=Ashcraft |first=Brian |date=September 4, 2013 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322200001/https://kotaku.com/animal-crossing-sure-looks-different-in-manga-form-1250063591 |archive-date=March 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Nintendo's official ''Animal Crossing'' [[Twitter]] account was named after Isabelle before the twitter account was turned over to Tom Nook. While under Isabelle, the account tweeted in the style of the character in order to remind players about current or forthcoming ''Animal Crossing'' titles.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2014/3/28/5555682/animal-crossing-interview-new-console-version-smartphones |title=Animal Crossing's creators on new console versions, mobile connectivity and fatigue |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |last=McWhertor |first=Michael |date=March 28, 2014 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322111930/https://www.polygon.com/2014/3/28/5555682/animal-crossing-interview-new-console-version-smartphones |archive-date=March 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nIsabelle has received generally positive reception since her debut, to the point that she has become the mascot of the ''Animal Crossing'' series.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-09-13-animal-crossing-headed-to-nintendo-switch |title=Animal Crossing for Nintendo Switch finally confirmed |work=[[Eurogamer]] |last=Phillips |first=Tom |date=September 13, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606075333/https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-09-13-animal-crossing-headed-to-nintendo-switch |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dailydot.com/parsec/animal-crossing-switch-tom-nook-memes/ |title=\u2018Animal Crossing\u2019 is coming to Switch\u2014and the news sparked Tom Nook memes |work=[[The Daily Dot]] |last=Vincent |first=Brittany |date=September 15, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190404181749/https://www.dailydot.com/parsec/animal-crossing-switch-tom-nook-memes/ |archive-date=April 4, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"usg\">{{cite web |url=https://www.usgamer.net/articles/smash-bros-ultimate-new-challenger-spotlight-animal-crossings-best-girl-gets-a-chance-to-shine-on-nintendos-big-stage |title=Smash Bros. Ultimate New Challenger Spotlight: Animal Crossing's Best Girl Gets a Chance to Shine on Nintendo's Big Stage |work=[[US Gamer]] |last=Oxford |first=Nadia |date=September 14, 2018 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180915194711/https://www.usgamer.net/articles/smash-bros-ultimate-new-challenger-spotlight-animal-crossings-best-girl-gets-a-chance-to-shine-on-nintendos-big-stage |archive-date=September 15, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.geek.com/games/the-ultimate-super-smash-bros-character-guide-isabelle-1761623/ |title=The Ultimate Super Smash Bros. Character Guide: Isabelle |work=Geek.com |last=Minor |first=Jordan |date=November 20, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190602213400/https://www.geek.com/games/the-ultimate-super-smash-bros-character-guide-isabelle-1761623/ |archive-date=June 2, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://kotaku.com/every-costume-in-super-mario-maker-1730084595 |title=Every Costume In Super Mario Maker |work=[[Kotaku]] |last=Hernandez |first=Patricia |date=September 11, 2015 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606073836/https://kotaku.com/every-costume-in-super-mario-maker-1730084595 |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/06/21/animal-crossing-amiibo-appear-on-nintendo-website/155384/ |title=Animal Crossing amiibo Appear on Nintendo Website |work=Hardcore Gamer |last=Whritenour |first=Jacob |date=June 21, 2015 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606073839/https://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/06/21/animal-crossing-amiibo-appear-on-nintendo-website/155384/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> She was ranked as the as one of the best video game characters of the 2010s by ''Polygon'' staff; writer Nicole Carpenter called her a \"pure, helpful pal\" and a \"very real icon.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/features/2019/11/27/20974490/greatest-video-game-characters-2019-2010-skyrim-witcher-splatoon |title=The 70 best video game characters of the decade |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |last=Carpenter |first=Nicole |date=November 27, 2019 |accessdate=December 30, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200101231120/https://www.polygon.com/features/2019/11/27/20974490/greatest-video-game-characters-2019-2010-skyrim-witcher-splatoon |archive-date=January 1, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Writer Amy Valens explains that her popularity was due to her being \"wholesome, positive, and adorable.\" Writer Nadia Oxford praised her for her intelligence and selflessness, stating that she is \"guaranteed to turn your heart into a crimson puddle of pulsating goo.\"<ref name=\"usg\"/> She also noted that all Nintendo has to do to get her to go back to playing ''New Leaf'' is for them to \"release a sketch of Isabelle the shih tzu sitting forlornly at her cobweb-covered desk, a cup of coffee turning to ice by her elbow.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.usgamer.net/articles/why-does-everyone-keep-playing-animal-crossing |title=Why Does Everyone Keep Playing Animal Crossing? |work=[[US Gamer]] |last=Oxford |first=Nadia |date=August 8, 2013 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606074727/https://www.usgamer.net/articles/why-does-everyone-keep-playing-animal-crossing |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Kotaku]]'s Patricia Hernandez called Isabelle adorable and her \"beloved,\" while expressing sadness at how difficult it was to obtain her [[amiibo|amiibo card]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://kotaku.com/i-bought-five-packs-of-animal-crossing-amiibo-cards-and-1733079601 |title=I Bought Five Packs of Animal Crossing Amiibo Cards And Didn\u2019t Fucking Get Isabelle |work=[[Kotaku]] |last=Hernandez |first=Patricia |date=September 25, 2015 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190518075209/https://kotaku.com/i-bought-five-packs-of-animal-crossing-amiibo-cards-and-1733079601 |archive-date=May 18, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n[[GamesRadar]]'s Henry Gilbert called her his favorite resident in ''Animal Crossing'' due to her cute appearance and reliability.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gamesradar.com/animal-crossing-figure-cute-it-versatile/ |title=This Animal Crossing figure is as cute as it is versatile |work=[[GamesRadar]] |last=Gilbert |first=Henry |date=August 22, 2014 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606080108/https://www.gamesradar.com/animal-crossing-figure-cute-it-versatile/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Writer Brittany Vincent called Isabelle one of the most adorable ''Animal Crossing'' characters.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.destructoid.com/this-isabelle-purse-is-absolutely-adorable-281999.phtml |title=This Isabelle purse is absolutely adorable |work=[[Destructoid]] |last=Vincent |first=Brittany |date=October 1, 2010 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160405024841/http://www.destructoid.com/this-isabelle-purse-is-absolutely-adorable-281999.phtml |archive-date=April 5, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> Writer Jaime Carrillo called her the best helper in video games.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dailydot.com/bazaar/isabelle-plush/ |title=This Isabelle plush is the most precious mayor\u2019s assistant ever |work=[[The Daily Dot]] |last=Carrillo |first=Jaime |date=March 22, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606080004/https://www.dailydot.com/bazaar/isabelle-plush/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Author Ashley Brown discussed ''Animal Crossing''{{'}}s systems where characters in the game are designed to be aware of the passage of time. She discussed Isabelle's dialogue in particular, where she will become flustered if the player chooses to try and delete the town. She brings up the residents and the town's history, which Brown says is a novel concept but one that may cause distress.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://e-channel.med.utah.edu/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/digra2015_BROWN.pdf |title=Animal Crossing: New Leaf and theDiversity of Horror in Video Games |work=[[University of Sk\u00f6vde]] |last=Brown |first=Ashley |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606090832/https://e-channel.med.utah.edu/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/digra2015_BROWN.pdf |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Isabelle has been perceived by fans as being [[pansexual]], hinted at by an apparent [[Limerence|crush]] on the player-character regardless of gender.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://junkee.com/isabelle-animal-crossing/202724|title=Isabelle From Animal Crossing Is 2019's Most Powerful Queer Icon|last=|first=|date=2019-04-26|website=[[Junkee]]|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191029194555/https://junkee.com/isabelle-animal-crossing/202724|archive-date=2019-10-29|access-date=2019-09-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mashable.com/article/nintendo-queer-memes/|title=All the best queer memes inspired by Nintendo|last=Dockray|first=Xavier Piedra and Heather|website=[[Mashable]]|language=en|access-date=2019-11-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825012647/https://mashable.com/article/nintendo-queer-memes/|archive-date=2019-08-25|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIsabelle has been a popular suggestion for ''[[Super Smash Bros. Ultimate]]'' among fans.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://comicbook.com/gaming/2018/09/13/super-smash-bros-ultimate-isabelle-animal-crossing/ |title='Animal Crossing' Favorite Isabelle Joins 'Super Smash Bros. Ultimate' Roster |work=Comic Book |last=Hayes |first=Matthew |date=September 13, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606090846/https://comicbook.com/gaming/2018/09/13/super-smash-bros-ultimate-isabelle-animal-crossing/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[Electronic Gaming Monthly]]'' writer Mollie L. Patterson praised her inclusion in ''Mario Kart 8'', calling her adorable and stating her infatuation with the character.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.egmnow.com/articles/reviews/egm-review-animal-crossing-new-leaf/ |title=Animal Crossing: New Leaf review |work=[[Electronic Gaming Monthly]] |last=Patterson |first=Mollie L. |date=June 4, 2013 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606074726/http://www.egmnow.com/articles/reviews/egm-review-animal-crossing-new-leaf/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.egmnow.com/articles/news/upcoming-mario-kart-8-dlc-brings-link-isabelle-new-tracks-and-more/ |title=Upcoming Mario Kart 8 DLC brings Link, Isabelle, new tracks, and more |work=[[Electronic Gaming Monthly]] |last=Patterson |first=Mollie L. |date=August 27, 2014 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606081835/https://www.egmnow.com/articles/news/upcoming-mario-kart-8-dlc-brings-link-isabelle-new-tracks-and-more/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Nadia Oxford considered Isabelle as part of one of the best downloadable content packs in 2015, calling her adorable.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.usgamer.net/articles/the-best-dlc-for-2015 |title=The Best DLC for 2015 |work=[[US Gamer]] |last=Oxford |first=Nadia |date=October 1, 2015 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606092008/https://www.usgamer.net/articles/the-best-dlc-for-2015 |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Writer Gita Jackson called Isabelle her \"precious angel\" and that Isabelle appearing in ''Super Smash Bros. Ultimate'' constituted a [[birthday]] gift to her.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://kotaku.com/the-internet-reacts-to-animal-crossings-isabelle-in-sma-1829058022 |title=The Internet Reacts To Animal Crossing's Isabelle In Smash |work=[[Kotaku]] |last=Jackson |first=Gita |date=September 14, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606074713/https://kotaku.com/the-internet-reacts-to-animal-crossings-isabelle-in-sma-1829058022 |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[Game Informer]]''{{'}}s Jeff Cork noted that Isabelle was a particular favorite for him among ''Ultimate''{{'}}s newcomers.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gameinformer.com/2018/12/06/wheres-our-super-smash-bros-ultimate-review |title=Where's Our Super Smash Bros. Ultimate Review? |work=[[Game Informer]] |last=Cork |first=Jeff |date=December 6, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606073839/https://www.gameinformer.com/2018/12/06/wheres-our-super-smash-bros-ultimate-review |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Writer Jeremy Parish ranked Isabelle as his 11th best character in ''Super Smash Bros. Ultimate''. He called her the \"most lovable, loyal, hard-working character\" Nintendo has.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/features/2018/12/3/18120401/super-smash-bros-ultimate-character-rankings |title=We rank the Smash Bros. (and friends) |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |last=Parish |first=Jeremy |date=December 3, 2018 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322075054/https://www.polygon.com/features/2018/12/3/18120401/super-smash-bros-ultimate-character-rankings |archive-date=March 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> She is also his favorite character in ''Mario Kart 8 Deluxe''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://retronauts.com/article/305/mario-kart-8-deluxe-the-retronauts-review |title=Mario Kart 8 Deluxe: The Retronauts review |work=[[Retronauts]] |last=Parish |first=Jeremy |date=April 25, 2017 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606080006/https://retronauts.com/article/305/mario-kart-8-deluxe-the-retronauts-review |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Paste Magazine]] writer Holly Green ranked her as her least favorite of the newcomers in ''Ultimate'', noting her dislike of some of her moves while praising her Fishing Rod attack.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2018/12/super-smash-bros-ultimate-new-fighters.html |title=Ranking Super Smash Bros Ultimate's New Fighters |work=[[Paste Magazine]] |last=Green |first=Holly |date=December 26, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606085137/https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2018/12/super-smash-bros-ultimate-new-fighters.html |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Fellow Paste Magazine writer Natalie Flores called her the cutest character in ''Super Smash Bros.''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2018/09/all-the-news-from-the-sept-13-nintendo-direct-draf.html |title=Here's Everything Nintendo Announced at Their Latest Direct |work=[[Paste Magazine]] |last=Flores |first=Natalie |date=September 14, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606075959/https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2018/09/all-the-news-from-the-sept-13-nintendo-direct-draf.html |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[IGN]]'s Tom Marks felt that she \"fantastic\" and \"charming,\" but lamented how similar she is to Villager.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2018/12/06/super-smash-bros-ultimate-review |title=Super Smash Bros. Ultimate Review |work=[[IGN]] |last=Marks |first=Tom |date=December 4, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190625131149/https://www.ign.com/articles/2018/12/06/super-smash-bros-ultimate-review |archive-date=June 25, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Merchandise and promotion==\nThe official ''Animal Crossing'' [[Twitter]] account was designed to appear as if it is Isabelle's<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gamerevolution.com/news/7635-animal-crossing-devs-taking-questions-via-twitter-for-gdc-panel |title=Animal Crossing Devs Taking Questions via Twitter for GDC Panel |work=Game Revolution |last=Bischoff |first=Daniel |date=March 13, 2014 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190607011622/https://www.gamerevolution.com/news/7635-animal-crossing-devs-taking-questions-via-twitter-for-gdc-panel |archive-date=June 7, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>, until the release of ''[[Animal Crossing: New Horizons]]''. An ''Animal Crossing''-brand Isabelle [[amiibo]] was produced in conjunction with the release of ''Animal Crossing: amiibo Festival''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2015/6/16/8789807/animal-crossing-amiibo-festival-wii-u |title=Animal Crossing: amiibo Festival coming to Wii U, plus four new Animal Crossing amiibo |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |last=Sarkar |first=Samit |date=June 16, 2015 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6ZKjjsmrE?url=http://www.polygon.com/2015/6/16/8789807/animal-crossing-amiibo-festival-wii-u |archive-date=June 16, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref> A ''Super Smash Bros.'' amiibo based on her appearance in ''Super Smash Bros. Ultimate'' was announced for 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/nintendo/2018/11/1/18051804/super-smash-bros-ultimate-amiibos-release-dates |title=Super Smash Bros. Ultimate\u2019s next wave of amiibo includes Isabelle, Pichu |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |last=Radulovic |first=Petrana |date=November 1, 2018 |accessdate=March 22, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181101201124/https://www.polygon.com/nintendo/2018/11/1/18051804/super-smash-bros-ultimate-amiibos-release-dates |archive-date=November 1, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> The Isabelle amiibo sold out immediately, which caused writer Chris Carter surprise due to otherwise low sales of ''Animal Crossing'' amiibo.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.destructoid.com/the-next-wave-of-smash-amiibo-are-on-sale-now-isabelle-sells-out-instantly-550768.phtml |title=The next wave of Smash amiibo are on sale now, Isabelle sells out instantly |work=[[Destructoid]] |last=Carter |first=Chris |date=April 19, 2019 |accessdate=June 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[New Nintendo 3DS]] owners were able to swap out the default faceplates for faceplates featuring Isabelle.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2014/8/29/6084277/nintendo-3ds-themes |title=Themes are coming to Nintendo 3DS to make your old 3DS prettier |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |last=McWhertor |first=Michael |date=August 29, 2014 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322111928/https://www.polygon.com/2014/8/29/6084277/nintendo-3ds-themes |archive-date=March 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> A [[Nendoroid]] figurine of Isabelle was released by [[Good Smile]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2015/12/15/animal-crossings-isabelle-now-in-nendoroid-form |title=Animal Crossing's Isabelle, Now in Nendoroid Form |work=[[IGN]] |last=Carpenter |first=Nicole |date=December 15, 2015 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322111926/https://www.ign.com/articles/2015/12/15/animal-crossings-isabelle-now-in-nendoroid-form |archive-date=March 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> A crossover promotion between [[Sanrio]] and ''Animal Crossing'' lead to a digital menu theme depicting [[Hello Kitty]] and Isabelle in a truck.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.siliconera.com/2016/11/04/isabelle-meets-hello-kitty-animal-crossing-x-sanrios-3ds-collaboration-themes/ |title=Isabelle Meets Hello Kitty In Animal Crossing X Sanrio\u2019s 3DS Collaboration Themes |author=Casey |date=November 4, 2016 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606065925/https://www.siliconera.com/2016/11/04/isabelle-meets-hello-kitty-animal-crossing-x-sanrios-3ds-collaboration-themes/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Multiple [[Line (software)|Line]] digital stickers featuring Isabelle were released on the app.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nintendoworldreport.com/news/41215/animal-crossing-characters-available-in-line-messaging-app |title=Animal Crossing Characters Available in LINE Messaging App |work=Nintendo World Report |last=Abou-Nasr |first=Adam |date=September 14, 2015 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606073836/http://www.nintendoworldreport.com/news/41215/animal-crossing-characters-available-in-line-messaging-app |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n{{Animal Crossing}}\n{{Super Smash Bros.}}\n\n[[Category:Animal Crossing characters]]\n[[Category:Anthropomorphic dogs]]\n[[Category:Female characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Fictional secretaries]]\n[[Category:Fictional dogs]]\n[[Category:Super Smash Bros. fighters]]\n[[Category:Video game characters introduced in 2012]]\n[[Category:Video game mascots]]\n[[Category:Nintendo protagonists]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Fictional character from the Animal Crossing franchise}}\n{{italic title|noerror|string=Animal Crossing|all=yes}}\n{{Infobox character\n| color              = yellow\n| image              = File:Isabelle AF.png\n| caption            = Isabelle as featured in promotional art for ''[[Animal Crossing: New Horizons]]''\n| name               = Isabelle\n| series             = [[Animal Crossing]]\n| firstgame          = ''[[Animal Crossing: New Leaf]]'' (2012)\n| creator            = \n| voice              = \n| origin             = \n| nationality        = \n| family             = Digby (twin brother)\n| occupation         = Secretary\n| species = [[Dog]], [[Shih Tzu]]\n}}\n'''Isabelle''', known as {{nihongo|'''Shizue'''|\u3057\u305a\u3048}} in Japan, is a fictional character from the ''[[Animal Crossing]]'' series of video games. She is a kindly [[Shih Tzu]] that debuted in the 2012 release ''[[Animal Crossing: New Leaf]]'', where she serves as the secretary to the player character. Isabelle has received positive reception, to the point of becoming one of the most prominent characters in the ''Animal Crossing'' franchise and its ''de facto'' mascot. Her popularity has also led to appearances outside of the ''Animal Crossing'' series, including a playable role in the crossover fighting game ''[[Super Smash Bros. Ultimate]]''.\n\n==Concept and creation==\nIsabelle is a golden-coloured [[Shih Tzu]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.polygon.com/e3/2019/6/12/18662876/isabelle-animal-crossing-new-horizons-nintendo-switch-e3-2019-return|title=Hooray: Isabelle will be in Animal Crossing: New Horizons|last=Hernandez|first=Patricia|date=2019-06-12|website=Polygon|language=en|access-date=2019-12-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200101163840/https://www.polygon.com/e3/2019/6/12/18662876/isabelle-animal-crossing-new-horizons-nintendo-switch-e3-2019-return|archive-date=2020-01-01|url-status=live}}</ref> originally named Shizue in Japanese.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nintendojo.com/features/editorials/evaluating-localization-in-defense-of-noa-treehouse |title=Evaluating Localization: In Defense of NOA Treehouse |work=Nintendojo |last=Pelone |first=Anthony |date=April 6, 2016 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606092001/http://www.nintendojo.com/features/editorials/evaluating-localization-in-defense-of-noa-treehouse |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Animal Crossing'' designers wanted players to reject Isabelle's offer of a ceremony for various accomplishments as mayor at least once so that they feel bad about having done so.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://iwataasks.nintendo.com/interviews/#/3ds/animalcrossing-newleaf/0/1 |title=Nintendo 3DS |work=[[Nintendo]] |last=Iwata |first=Satoru |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190622234955/http://iwataasks.nintendo.com/interviews/#/3ds/animalcrossing-newleaf/0/1 |archive-date=June 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''Animal Crossing'' director Katsuya Eguchi and ''New Leaf'' producer [[Aya Kyogoku]] both enjoyed Isabelle; Eguchi appreciated her for her smile, friendliness, and clumsiness.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2016/08/25/we-asked-splatoons-producers-to-pick-sides-in-splatfest |title=We Asked Splatoon\u2019s Producers to Pick Sides in Splatfest |work=[[IGN]] |date=August 25, 2016 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606064041/https://www.ign.com/articles/2016/08/25/we-asked-splatoons-producers-to-pick-sides-in-splatfest |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mtv.com/news/2467124/animal-crossing-favorite-characters/ |title='Animal Crossing' Developers Pick Their Favorite Characters |work=[[MTV]] |last=Cipriano |first=Jason |date=May 15, 2013 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606091956/http://www.mtv.com/news/2467124/animal-crossing-favorite-characters/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nIsabelle's appearance in ''[[Super Smash Bros. Ultimate]]'' is based on fellow ''Animal Crossing'' character [[Villager (Animal Crossing)|Villager]]. However, ''Super Smash Bros.'' series director [[Masahiro Sakurai]] chose not to make Isabelle an \"Echo Fighter\" (a character with relatively minor differences from another) of Villager because of her different animations and her proportions being based on character models in ''[[Animal Crossing: New Leaf]]'', as opposed to earlier ''Animal Crossing'' character models.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.siliconera.com/2018/09/29/sakurai-talks-about-why-isabelle-isnt-an-echo-fighter-and-the-chaos-that-is-smash-bros/ |title=Sakurai Talks About Why Isabelle Isn\u2019t An Echo Fighter, And The Chaos That Is Smash Bros. |work=[[Siliconera]] |last=Wong |first=Alistair |date=September 29, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606071437/https://www.siliconera.com/2018/09/29/sakurai-talks-about-why-isabelle-isnt-an-echo-fighter-and-the-chaos-that-is-smash-bros/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Appearances==\nIsabelle first appeared in the 2012 video game ''[[Animal Crossing: New Leaf]]'' along with her twin brother [[Digby (Animal Crossing)|Digby]]. In the game, she acts as the secretary to the player character, who becomes the town mayor, and assists them with various tasks. She has appeared in several ''Animal Crossing'' games since, including ''[[Animal Crossing: Happy Home Designer]]'', ''[[Animal Crossing: amiibo Festival]]'', ''[[Animal Crossing: Pocket Camp]] and [[Animal Crossing: New Horizons]].''\n\nOutside of the ''Animal Crossing'' franchise, Isabelle has also appeared in the ''[[Super Smash Bros.]]'' series, first appearing as an assist trophy in ''[[Super Smash Bros. for Nintendo 3DS and Wii U]]'' before becoming a playable fighter in the [[Nintendo Switch]] sequel ''[[Super Smash Bros. Ultimate]]''. Isabelle also appears in the [[Wii U]] video game ''[[Mario Kart 8]]'' as a downloadable racer, as well as in its Nintendo Switch port ''[[Mario Kart 8 Deluxe]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2015/4/1/8328155/mario-kart-8-animal-crossing-dlc-release-date-price |title=Mario Kart 8's Animal Crossing DLC arrives early on April 23 |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |last=Sarkar |first=Samit |date=April 1, 2015 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322194837/https://www.polygon.com/2015/4/1/8328155/mario-kart-8-animal-crossing-dlc-release-date-price |archive-date=March 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Player costumes based on Isabelle appear in ''[[Super Mario Maker]]'' and ''[[Monster Hunter 4|Monster Hunter 4 Ultimate]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2015/6/5/8737331/monster-hunter-4-animal-crossing-devil-may-cry |title=Animal Crossing, Devil May Cry and more come to Monster Hunter 4 this month |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |last=McWhertor |first=Michael |date=June 5, 2015 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322194837/https://www.polygon.com/2015/6/5/8737331/monster-hunter-4-animal-crossing-devil-may-cry |archive-date=March 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Isabelle also appears as part of Nintendo's [[amiibo]] line of [[toys-to-life]] figures. She has 2 figures from the Animal Crossing line, 1 from the Smash Bros line, and several different Animal Crossing amiibo cards. \n\n===In other media===\nIsabelle appears in a one-off gag manga in the magazine ''[[CoroCoro]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://kotaku.com/animal-crossing-sure-looks-different-in-manga-form-1250063591 |title=Animal Crossing Sure Looks... Different in Manga Form |work=[[Kotaku]] |last=Ashcraft |first=Brian |date=September 4, 2013 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322200001/https://kotaku.com/animal-crossing-sure-looks-different-in-manga-form-1250063591 |archive-date=March 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Nintendo's official ''Animal Crossing'' [[Twitter]] account was named after Isabelle before the twitter account was turned over to Tom Nook. While under Isabelle, the account tweeted in the style of the character in order to remind players about current or forthcoming ''Animal Crossing'' titles.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2014/3/28/5555682/animal-crossing-interview-new-console-version-smartphones |title=Animal Crossing's creators on new console versions, mobile connectivity and fatigue |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |last=McWhertor |first=Michael |date=March 28, 2014 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322111930/https://www.polygon.com/2014/3/28/5555682/animal-crossing-interview-new-console-version-smartphones |archive-date=March 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nIsabelle has received generally positive reception since her debut, to the point that she has become the mascot of the ''Animal Crossing'' series.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-09-13-animal-crossing-headed-to-nintendo-switch |title=Animal Crossing for Nintendo Switch finally confirmed |work=[[Eurogamer]] |last=Phillips |first=Tom |date=September 13, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606075333/https://www.eurogamer.net/articles/2018-09-13-animal-crossing-headed-to-nintendo-switch |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dailydot.com/parsec/animal-crossing-switch-tom-nook-memes/ |title=\u2018Animal Crossing\u2019 is coming to Switch\u2014and the news sparked Tom Nook memes |work=[[The Daily Dot]] |last=Vincent |first=Brittany |date=September 15, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190404181749/https://www.dailydot.com/parsec/animal-crossing-switch-tom-nook-memes/ |archive-date=April 4, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"usg\">{{cite web |url=https://www.usgamer.net/articles/smash-bros-ultimate-new-challenger-spotlight-animal-crossings-best-girl-gets-a-chance-to-shine-on-nintendos-big-stage |title=Smash Bros. Ultimate New Challenger Spotlight: Animal Crossing's Best Girl Gets a Chance to Shine on Nintendo's Big Stage |work=[[US Gamer]] |last=Oxford |first=Nadia |date=September 14, 2018 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180915194711/https://www.usgamer.net/articles/smash-bros-ultimate-new-challenger-spotlight-animal-crossings-best-girl-gets-a-chance-to-shine-on-nintendos-big-stage |archive-date=September 15, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.geek.com/games/the-ultimate-super-smash-bros-character-guide-isabelle-1761623/ |title=The Ultimate Super Smash Bros. Character Guide: Isabelle |work=Geek.com |last=Minor |first=Jordan |date=November 20, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190602213400/https://www.geek.com/games/the-ultimate-super-smash-bros-character-guide-isabelle-1761623/ |archive-date=June 2, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://kotaku.com/every-costume-in-super-mario-maker-1730084595 |title=Every Costume In Super Mario Maker |work=[[Kotaku]] |last=Hernandez |first=Patricia |date=September 11, 2015 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606073836/https://kotaku.com/every-costume-in-super-mario-maker-1730084595 |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/06/21/animal-crossing-amiibo-appear-on-nintendo-website/155384/ |title=Animal Crossing amiibo Appear on Nintendo Website |work=Hardcore Gamer |last=Whritenour |first=Jacob |date=June 21, 2015 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606073839/https://www.hardcoregamer.com/2015/06/21/animal-crossing-amiibo-appear-on-nintendo-website/155384/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> She was ranked as the as one of the best video game characters of the 2010s by ''Polygon'' staff; writer Nicole Carpenter called her a \"pure, helpful pal\" and a \"very real icon.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/features/2019/11/27/20974490/greatest-video-game-characters-2019-2010-skyrim-witcher-splatoon |title=The 70 best video game characters of the decade |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |last=Carpenter |first=Nicole |date=November 27, 2019 |accessdate=December 30, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200101231120/https://www.polygon.com/features/2019/11/27/20974490/greatest-video-game-characters-2019-2010-skyrim-witcher-splatoon |archive-date=January 1, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref> Writer Amy Valens explains that her popularity was due to her being \"wholesome, positive, and adorable.\" Writer Nadia Oxford praised her for her intelligence and selflessness, stating that she is \"guaranteed to turn your heart into a crimson puddle of pulsating goo.\"<ref name=\"usg\"/> She also noted that all Nintendo has to do to get her to go back to playing ''New Leaf'' is for them to \"release a sketch of Isabelle the shih tzu sitting forlornly at her cobweb-covered desk, a cup of coffee turning to ice by her elbow.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.usgamer.net/articles/why-does-everyone-keep-playing-animal-crossing |title=Why Does Everyone Keep Playing Animal Crossing? |work=[[US Gamer]] |last=Oxford |first=Nadia |date=August 8, 2013 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606074727/https://www.usgamer.net/articles/why-does-everyone-keep-playing-animal-crossing |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Kotaku]]'s Patricia Hernandez called Isabelle adorable and her \"beloved,\" while expressing sadness at how difficult it was to obtain her [[amiibo|amiibo card]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://kotaku.com/i-bought-five-packs-of-animal-crossing-amiibo-cards-and-1733079601 |title=I Bought Five Packs of Animal Crossing Amiibo Cards And Didn\u2019t Fucking Get Isabelle |work=[[Kotaku]] |last=Hernandez |first=Patricia |date=September 25, 2015 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190518075209/https://kotaku.com/i-bought-five-packs-of-animal-crossing-amiibo-cards-and-1733079601 |archive-date=May 18, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n[[GamesRadar]]'s Henry Gilbert called her his favorite resident in ''Animal Crossing'' due to her cute appearance and reliability.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gamesradar.com/animal-crossing-figure-cute-it-versatile/ |title=This Animal Crossing figure is as cute as it is versatile |work=[[GamesRadar]] |last=Gilbert |first=Henry |date=August 22, 2014 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606080108/https://www.gamesradar.com/animal-crossing-figure-cute-it-versatile/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Writer Brittany Vincent called Isabelle one of the most adorable ''Animal Crossing'' characters.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.destructoid.com/this-isabelle-purse-is-absolutely-adorable-281999.phtml |title=This Isabelle purse is absolutely adorable |work=[[Destructoid]] |last=Vincent |first=Brittany |date=October 1, 2010 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160405024841/http://www.destructoid.com/this-isabelle-purse-is-absolutely-adorable-281999.phtml |archive-date=April 5, 2016 |url-status=live }}</ref> Writer Jaime Carrillo called her the best helper in video games.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dailydot.com/bazaar/isabelle-plush/ |title=This Isabelle plush is the most precious mayor\u2019s assistant ever |work=[[The Daily Dot]] |last=Carrillo |first=Jaime |date=March 22, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606080004/https://www.dailydot.com/bazaar/isabelle-plush/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Author Ashley Brown discussed ''Animal Crossing''{{'}}s systems where characters in the game are designed to be aware of the passage of time. She discussed Isabelle's dialogue in particular, where she will become flustered if the player chooses to try and delete the town. She brings up the residents and the town's history, which Brown says is a novel concept but one that may cause distress.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://e-channel.med.utah.edu/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/digra2015_BROWN.pdf |title=Animal Crossing: New Leaf and theDiversity of Horror in Video Games |work=[[University of Sk\u00f6vde]] |last=Brown |first=Ashley |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606090832/https://e-channel.med.utah.edu/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/digra2015_BROWN.pdf |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Isabelle has been perceived by fans as being [[pansexual]], hinted at by an apparent [[Limerence|crush]] on the player-character regardless of gender.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://junkee.com/isabelle-animal-crossing/202724|title=Isabelle From Animal Crossing Is 2019's Most Powerful Queer Icon|last=|first=|date=2019-04-26|website=[[Junkee]]|language=en-US|url-status=live|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191029194555/https://junkee.com/isabelle-animal-crossing/202724|archive-date=2019-10-29|access-date=2019-09-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://mashable.com/article/nintendo-queer-memes/|title=All the best queer memes inspired by Nintendo|last=Dockray|first=Xavier Piedra and Heather|website=[[Mashable]]|language=en|access-date=2019-11-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190825012647/https://mashable.com/article/nintendo-queer-memes/|archive-date=2019-08-25|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIsabelle has been a popular suggestion for ''[[Super Smash Bros. Ultimate]]'' among fans.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://comicbook.com/gaming/2018/09/13/super-smash-bros-ultimate-isabelle-animal-crossing/ |title='Animal Crossing' Favorite Isabelle Joins 'Super Smash Bros. Ultimate' Roster |work=Comic Book |last=Hayes |first=Matthew |date=September 13, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606090846/https://comicbook.com/gaming/2018/09/13/super-smash-bros-ultimate-isabelle-animal-crossing/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[Electronic Gaming Monthly]]'' writer Mollie L. Patterson praised her inclusion in ''Mario Kart 8'', calling her adorable and stating her infatuation with the character.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.egmnow.com/articles/reviews/egm-review-animal-crossing-new-leaf/ |title=Animal Crossing: New Leaf review |work=[[Electronic Gaming Monthly]] |last=Patterson |first=Mollie L. |date=June 4, 2013 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606074726/http://www.egmnow.com/articles/reviews/egm-review-animal-crossing-new-leaf/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.egmnow.com/articles/news/upcoming-mario-kart-8-dlc-brings-link-isabelle-new-tracks-and-more/ |title=Upcoming Mario Kart 8 DLC brings Link, Isabelle, new tracks, and more |work=[[Electronic Gaming Monthly]] |last=Patterson |first=Mollie L. |date=August 27, 2014 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606081835/https://www.egmnow.com/articles/news/upcoming-mario-kart-8-dlc-brings-link-isabelle-new-tracks-and-more/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Nadia Oxford considered Isabelle as part of one of the best downloadable content packs in 2015, calling her adorable.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.usgamer.net/articles/the-best-dlc-for-2015 |title=The Best DLC for 2015 |work=[[US Gamer]] |last=Oxford |first=Nadia |date=October 1, 2015 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606092008/https://www.usgamer.net/articles/the-best-dlc-for-2015 |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Writer Gita Jackson called Isabelle her \"precious angel\" and that Isabelle appearing in ''Super Smash Bros. Ultimate'' constituted a [[birthday]] gift to her.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://kotaku.com/the-internet-reacts-to-animal-crossings-isabelle-in-sma-1829058022 |title=The Internet Reacts To Animal Crossing's Isabelle In Smash |work=[[Kotaku]] |last=Jackson |first=Gita |date=September 14, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606074713/https://kotaku.com/the-internet-reacts-to-animal-crossings-isabelle-in-sma-1829058022 |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> ''[[Game Informer]]''{{'}}s Jeff Cork noted that Isabelle was a particular favorite for him among ''Ultimate''{{'}}s newcomers.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gameinformer.com/2018/12/06/wheres-our-super-smash-bros-ultimate-review |title=Where's Our Super Smash Bros. Ultimate Review? |work=[[Game Informer]] |last=Cork |first=Jeff |date=December 6, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606073839/https://www.gameinformer.com/2018/12/06/wheres-our-super-smash-bros-ultimate-review |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Writer Jeremy Parish ranked Isabelle as his 11th best character in ''Super Smash Bros. Ultimate''. He called her the \"most lovable, loyal, hard-working character\" Nintendo has.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/features/2018/12/3/18120401/super-smash-bros-ultimate-character-rankings |title=We rank the Smash Bros. (and friends) |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |last=Parish |first=Jeremy |date=December 3, 2018 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322075054/https://www.polygon.com/features/2018/12/3/18120401/super-smash-bros-ultimate-character-rankings |archive-date=March 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> She is also his favorite character in ''Mario Kart 8 Deluxe''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://retronauts.com/article/305/mario-kart-8-deluxe-the-retronauts-review |title=Mario Kart 8 Deluxe: The Retronauts review |work=[[Retronauts]] |last=Parish |first=Jeremy |date=April 25, 2017 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606080006/https://retronauts.com/article/305/mario-kart-8-deluxe-the-retronauts-review |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[Paste Magazine]] writer Holly Green ranked her as her least favorite of the newcomers in ''Ultimate'', noting her dislike of some of her moves while praising her Fishing Rod attack.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2018/12/super-smash-bros-ultimate-new-fighters.html |title=Ranking Super Smash Bros Ultimate's New Fighters |work=[[Paste Magazine]] |last=Green |first=Holly |date=December 26, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606085137/https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2018/12/super-smash-bros-ultimate-new-fighters.html |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Fellow Paste Magazine writer Natalie Flores called her the cutest character in ''Super Smash Bros.''<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2018/09/all-the-news-from-the-sept-13-nintendo-direct-draf.html |title=Here's Everything Nintendo Announced at Their Latest Direct |work=[[Paste Magazine]] |last=Flores |first=Natalie |date=September 14, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606075959/https://www.pastemagazine.com/articles/2018/09/all-the-news-from-the-sept-13-nintendo-direct-draf.html |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> [[IGN]]'s Tom Marks felt that she \"fantastic\" and \"charming,\" but lamented how similar she is to Villager.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2018/12/06/super-smash-bros-ultimate-review |title=Super Smash Bros. Ultimate Review |work=[[IGN]] |last=Marks |first=Tom |date=December 4, 2018 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190625131149/https://www.ign.com/articles/2018/12/06/super-smash-bros-ultimate-review |archive-date=June 25, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==Merchandise and promotion==\nThe official ''Animal Crossing'' [[Twitter]] account was designed to appear as if it is Isabelle's.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gamerevolution.com/news/7635-animal-crossing-devs-taking-questions-via-twitter-for-gdc-panel |title=Animal Crossing Devs Taking Questions via Twitter for GDC Panel |work=Game Revolution |last=Bischoff |first=Daniel |date=March 13, 2014 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190607011622/https://www.gamerevolution.com/news/7635-animal-crossing-devs-taking-questions-via-twitter-for-gdc-panel |archive-date=June 7, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>, until the release of [[Animal Crossing: New Horizons]]. An ''Animal Crossing''-brand Isabelle [[amiibo]] was produced in conjunction with the release of ''Animal Crossing: amiibo Festival''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2015/6/16/8789807/animal-crossing-amiibo-festival-wii-u |title=Animal Crossing: amiibo Festival coming to Wii U, plus four new Animal Crossing amiibo |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |last=Sarkar |first=Samit |date=June 16, 2015 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/6ZKjjsmrE?url=http://www.polygon.com/2015/6/16/8789807/animal-crossing-amiibo-festival-wii-u |archive-date=June 16, 2015 |url-status=live }}</ref> A ''Super Smash Bros.'' amiibo based on her appearance in ''Super Smash Bros. Ultimate'' was announced for 2019.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/nintendo/2018/11/1/18051804/super-smash-bros-ultimate-amiibos-release-dates |title=Super Smash Bros. Ultimate\u2019s next wave of amiibo includes Isabelle, Pichu |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |last=Radulovic |first=Petrana |date=November 1, 2018 |accessdate=March 22, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181101201124/https://www.polygon.com/nintendo/2018/11/1/18051804/super-smash-bros-ultimate-amiibos-release-dates |archive-date=November 1, 2018 |url-status=live }}</ref> The Isabelle amiibo sold out immediately, which caused writer Chris Carter surprise due to otherwise low sales of ''Animal Crossing'' amiibo.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.destructoid.com/the-next-wave-of-smash-amiibo-are-on-sale-now-isabelle-sells-out-instantly-550768.phtml |title=The next wave of Smash amiibo are on sale now, Isabelle sells out instantly |work=[[Destructoid]] |last=Carter |first=Chris |date=April 19, 2019 |accessdate=June 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n[[New Nintendo 3DS]] owners were able to swap out the default faceplates for faceplates featuring Isabelle.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.polygon.com/2014/8/29/6084277/nintendo-3ds-themes |title=Themes are coming to Nintendo 3DS to make your old 3DS prettier |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |last=McWhertor |first=Michael |date=August 29, 2014 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322111928/https://www.polygon.com/2014/8/29/6084277/nintendo-3ds-themes |archive-date=March 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> A [[Nendoroid]] figurine of Isabelle was released by [[Good Smile]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2015/12/15/animal-crossings-isabelle-now-in-nendoroid-form |title=Animal Crossing's Isabelle, Now in Nendoroid Form |work=[[IGN]] |last=Carpenter |first=Nicole |date=December 15, 2015 |accessdate=March 22, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190322111926/https://www.ign.com/articles/2015/12/15/animal-crossings-isabelle-now-in-nendoroid-form |archive-date=March 22, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> A crossover promotion between [[Sanrio]] and ''Animal Crossing'' lead to a digital menu theme depicting [[Hello Kitty]] and Isabelle in a truck.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.siliconera.com/2016/11/04/isabelle-meets-hello-kitty-animal-crossing-x-sanrios-3ds-collaboration-themes/ |title=Isabelle Meets Hello Kitty In Animal Crossing X Sanrio\u2019s 3DS Collaboration Themes |author=Casey |date=November 4, 2016 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606065925/https://www.siliconera.com/2016/11/04/isabelle-meets-hello-kitty-animal-crossing-x-sanrios-3ds-collaboration-themes/ |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> Multiple [[Line (software)|Line]] digital stickers featuring Isabelle were released on the app.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nintendoworldreport.com/news/41215/animal-crossing-characters-available-in-line-messaging-app |title=Animal Crossing Characters Available in LINE Messaging App |work=Nintendo World Report |last=Abou-Nasr |first=Adam |date=September 14, 2015 |accessdate=June 6, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190606073836/http://www.nintendoworldreport.com/news/41215/animal-crossing-characters-available-in-line-messaging-app |archive-date=June 6, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2}}\n\n{{Animal Crossing}}\n{{Super Smash Bros.}}\n\n[[Category:Animal Crossing characters]]\n[[Category:Anthropomorphic dogs]]\n[[Category:Female characters in video games]]\n[[Category:Fictional secretaries]]\n[[Category:Fictional dogs]]\n[[Category:Super Smash Bros. fighters]]\n[[Category:Video game characters introduced in 2012]]\n[[Category:Video game mascots]]\n[[Category:Nintendo protagonists]]\n", "name_user": "EmiOfBrie", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eMerchandise and promotion:formatting", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Isabelle_(Animal_Crossing)"}
{"title_page": "Dil Ek Mandir", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Dil Ek Mandir\n| image          = Dil Ek Mandir, 1963 film.jpg\n| caption        = Poster\n| director       = [[C. V. Sridhar]]\n| producer       = \n| story          = C.V. Sridhar\n| starring       = [[Rajendra Kumar]]<br />[[Meena Kumari]]<br />[[Raaj Kumar]]\n| music          = [[Shankar Jaikishan]]\n| cinematography = [[A. Vincent]]\n| editing        = N. M Shankar\n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|1963|3|8|df=yes}}<ref name=\"Release Date\">{{cite web |title= Dil Ek Mandir|website=Times of India |url= https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-details/dil-ek-mandir/movieshow/61347122.cms |accessdate= 2018-06-28}}</ref> \n| runtime        = \n| country        = India\n| language       = Hindi\n| gross          = {{INRConvert|1.1|c|year=1963}} <ref name=\"boi63\">{{cite web |url=http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=166&catName=MTk2MA== |title=Box Office 1963 |publisher=[[Box Office India]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120922021750/http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=166&catName=MTk2MA== |archivedate=22 September 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Dil Ek Mandir''''' ({{Literal translation|The heart is a temple}}) is a [[List of Bollywood films of 1963|1963]] Indian [[Hindi]]-language [[romantic drama]] film directed by [[C. V. Sridhar]]. The film stars [[Rajendra Kumar]], [[Meena Kumari]], [[Raaj Kumar]] and [[Mehmood Ali|Mehmood]]. The film's music is by [[Shankar Jaikishan]]. All the songs of this film were hits and were loved by everyone. The film was a major hit at the box office. Got No. 5 on box office collection list. The film was a remake of the [[Tamil language|Tamil]] film ''[[Nenjil Or Aalayam]]'' (1962), also directed by Sridhar.<ref name=\"thehindu\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/article788918.ece |title=Dil Ek Mandir (1963) |last=Mahaan |first=Deepak |date=29 January 2010 |work=[[The Hindu]] |access-date=10 April 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150929052051/http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/article788918.ece |archive-date=29 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n== Plot ==\nSita (Meena Kumari) is married to Ram (Raaj Kumar), who is diagnosed to have cancer. Ram is admitted to a hospital where he is to be treated by Dr. Dharmesh (Rajendra Kumar). Dr. Dharmesh is Sita's former love and both of them are very much uncomfortable to interact in front of Sita's husband. Sita suspects that Dr. Dharmesh will not be able to give her husband a fair treatment because of his love interest in her. When she mentions this to him he promises her that he will try his best to save her husband. Ram overhears this conversation and later suggests to Sita that she should marry Dr. Dharmesh after his death. Ram is to undergo a major surgery under Dr. Dharmesh, which will decide his fate. Dr. Dharmesh is seized with a feeling that he can't afford to fail in this surgery, as it might seem that he was biased due to Sita. He works hard for the preparation of the surgery, without proper food/sleep for a long time. Finally, at the end the surgery takes place. Dr. Dharmesh comes out from the operation theatre and tells Sita that the operation was successful and her husband is safe. He takes couple of steps forward and collapses. Long days of hard work for the preparation of surgery takes its toll, and he dies on the spot. The last scene shows Ram and Sita at the inauguration of a hospital built in Dr. Dharmesh's memory. Dr. Dharmesh's mother inaugurates his statue and everybody places flowers there.\n\n== Cast ==\n* [[Rajendra Kumar]]&nbsp;\u2013 Dr. Dharmesh<ref name=\"thehindu\" />\n* [[Meena Kumari]]&nbsp;\u2013 Sita<ref name=\"thehindu\" />\n* [[Raaj Kumar]]&nbsp;\u2013 Ram<ref name=\"thehindu\" />\n* [[Mehmood Ali|Mehmood]]&nbsp;\u2013 Lallu Lal\n* [[Kutty Padmini]]&nbsp;\u2013 Uma\n* [[Shubha Khote]]&nbsp;\u2013 Mynavati\n* [[Manmohan Krishna]]&nbsp;\u2013 Philip\n* [[Achala Sachdev]]&nbsp;\u2013 Dharmesh's mother\n\n== Production ==\n''Dil Ek Mandir'' was directed by [[C. V. Sridhar]] and remade from his own [[Tamil language|Tamil]] film ''[[Nenjil Or Aalayam]]'' (1962). The entire film was completed in 27 days.<ref name=\"thehindu\" />\n\n== Soundtrack ==\n{| border=\"4\" cellpadding=\"7\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" align=\"center\"\n! # !! Title !! Singer(s)!!Lyricist!! Duration\n|-\n| 1\n| \"Dil Ek Mandir Hai\"\n| [[Mohammed Rafi]], [[Suman Kalyanpur]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"| [[Hasrat Jaipuri]]\n| 04:25\n|-\n| 2\n| \"Tum Sab Ko Chhod Kar\"\n| Mohammed Rafi\n| 04:07\n|-\n| 3\n| \"Ham Tere Pyar Mein\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"|[[Lata Mangeshkar]]\n| 04:47\n|-\n| 4\n| \"Ruk Ja Raat\"\n| rowspan=\"4\"|[[Shailendra (lyricist)|Shailendra]]\n| 04:13\n|-\n| 5\n| \"Yaad Na Jaye Beete Dinon Ki\"\n| Mohammed Rafi\n| 04:23\n|-\n| 6\n| \"O Meri Ladli\"\n| Suman Kalyanpur\n| 04:19\n|-\n| 7\n| \"Paalanhaare Ram Hai\"\t<small>(Bhajan)</small>\n|[[S. Janaki]]\n| 02:17\n|}\n\n== Awards ==\nAt the [[11th Filmfare Awards]], Raaj Kumar won the [[Filmfare Award for Best Supporting Actor|Best Supporting Actor Award]] and Arjun Dev Rashk won [[Filmfare Award for Best Dialogue|Best Dialogue]].<ref name=\"thehindu\" />\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|0139157|Dil Ek Mandir}}\n\n{{C. V. Sridhar}}\n\n[[Category:1963 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:1960s Hindi-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by C. V. Sridhar]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Shankar Jaikishan]]\n[[Category:Hindi remakes of Tamil films]]\n[[Category:Indian romantic drama films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Dil Ek Mandir\n| image          = Dil Ek Mandir, 1963 film.jpg\n| caption        = Poster\n| director       = [[C. V. Sridhar]]\n| producer       = \n| story          = C.V. Sridhar\n| starring       = [[Rajendra Kumar]]<br />[[Meena Kumari]]<br />[[Raaj Kumar]]\n| music          = [[Shankar Jaikishan]]\n| cinematography = [[A. Vincent]]\n| editing        = N. M Shankar\n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|1963|3|8|df=yes}}<ref name=\"Release Date\">{{cite web |title= Dil Ek Mandir|website=Times of India |url= https://m.timesofindia.com/entertainment/hindi/movie-details/dil-ek-mandir/movieshow/61347122.cms |accessdate= 2018-06-28}}</ref> \n| runtime        = \n| country        = India\n| language       = Hindi\n| gross          = {{INRConvert|1.1|c|year=1963}} <ref name=\"boi63\">{{cite web |url=http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=166&catName=MTk2MA== |title=Box Office 1963 |publisher=[[Box Office India]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120922021750/http://boxofficeindia.com/showProd.php?itemCat=166&catName=MTk2MA== |archivedate=22 September 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Dil Ek Mandir''''' ({{Literal translation|The heart is a temple}}) is a [[List of Bollywood films of 1963|1963]] Indian [[Hindi]]-language [[romantic drama]] film directed by [[C. V. Sridhar]]. The film stars [[Rajendra Kumar]], [[Meena Kumari]], [[Raaj Kumar]] and [[Mehmood Ali|Mehmood]]. The film's music is by [[Shankar Jaikishan]]. All the songs of this film were hits and were loved by everyone. The film was a major hit at the box office. Got No. 5 on box office collection list. The film was a remake of the [[Tamil language|Tamil]] film ''[[Nenjil Or Aalayam]]'' (1962), also directed by Sridhar.<ref name=\"thehindu\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/article788918.ece |title=Dil Ek Mandir (1963) |last=Mahaan |first=Deepak |date=