{"title_page": "Tampa, Colorado", "text_new": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{db-afd}}\n<!-- {{Article for deletion/dated|page=Tampa, Colorado|timestamp=20200328213223|year=2020|month=March|day=28|substed=yes}}-->\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Tampa, Colorado|date=28 March 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{Infobox settlement\n|name                     = Tampa\n|official_name            = \n|settlement_type          = [[Unincorporated area|Unincorporated community]]\n|nickname                 = \n|motto                    =\n\n<!-- Images -->\n|image_skyline            = \n|imagesize                = \n|image_caption            = \n|image_flag               = \n|image_seal               =\n\n<!-- Maps -->\n|pushpin_map              = Colorado\n|pushpin_label_position   = <!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n|pushpin_map_caption      = Location within the state of Colorado\n|pushpin_mapsize          =\n|image_map                = \n|map_caption              = Location within Weld county\n|image_map1               = \n|mapsize1                 = \n|map_caption1             =\n\n<!-- Location -->\n|subdivision_type         = [[List of sovereign states|Country]]\n|subdivision_name         = United States\n|subdivision_type1        = [[U.S. state|State]]\n|subdivision_name1        = [[Colorado]]\n|subdivision_type2        = [[List of counties in Colorado|County]]\n|subdivision_name2        = [[Weld County, Colorado|Weld]]\n|government_footnotes     = \n|government_type          = \n|leader_title             =\n|leader_name              =\n|leader_title1            = \n|leader_name1             = \n|established_title        = \n|established_date         =\n\n<!-- Area -->\n|unit_pref                = Imperial\n|area_footnotes           = \n|area_magnitude           = \n|area_total_km2           = \n|area_land_km2            = \n|area_water_km2           =\n\n<!-- Population -->\n|population_as_of         = [[United States Census, 2000|2000]]\n|population_footnotes     = \n|population_total         = \n|population_density_km2   = auto\n\n<!-- General information -->\n|timezone                 = [[Mountain Time Zone|Mountain (MST)]]\n|utc_offset               = -7\n|timezone_DST             = MDT\n|utc_offset_DST           = -6\n|elevation_footnotes      = \n|elevation_ft             = \n|coordinates              = {{coord|40|9|0|N|104|27|20|W|region:US_type:city|display=inline,title}}\n\n<!-- Area/postal codes & others -->\n|postal_code_type         = [[ZIP code]]s\n|postal_code              = 80643\n|area_code                = \n|blank_name               = [[Federal Information Processing Standard|FIPS code]]\n|blank_info               =\n|blank1_name              = [[Geographic Names Information System|GNIS]] feature ID\n|blank1_info              =\n|website                  = \n|footnotes                = \n}}\n'''Tampa''' is an [[Unincorporated area|unincorporated community]] in [[Weld County, Colorado|Weld County]], [[Colorado]],  United States. The rural community is served by an 80643 [[ZIP code]].\n\nOld timers in the area advise that Tampa was a departure point for an old railroad spur called the Tampa Spur.  Tampa was located on the old CB&Q line (now BNSF, Burlington Northern, Santa Fe), about halfway between Roggen and Keenesburg.\n\nOld timers advise that the Tampa Spur was a 1.5-mile-long railroad spur between Tampa and a place to the south called Sheehan, near the Prospect Valley, and that the spur functioned as a sugar beet dump.  (A beet dump was an elevated facility that allowed farmers to deposit newly harvested produce into open railroad cars.)\n\nAccording to these old timers, the Tampa Spur was built in 1882. It was still on the railroad maps in 1983, but does not appear on current railroad maps.\n\n==Geography==\nTampa is located at 40.149982 degrees north, 104.455512 degrees west (27.1499982, -104.455512);<ref name=\"GR1\">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/geo/www/gazetteer/gazette.html|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate=2011-04-23|date=2011-02-12|title=US Gazetteer files: 2010, 2000, and 1990}}</ref> or about 5.5 miles northeast of [[Keenesburg, Colorado|Keenesburg]].<ref>[http://colorado.hometownlocator.com/maps/distance-directions.cfm?tampa@40.1499824524,-104.455513 Distance & Driving Directions between Tampa and Keensburg]</ref> The [[elevation]] for the community is 4,813 feet above [[sea level]].<ref>[http://colorado.hometownlocator.com/co/weld/tampa.cfm Tampa profile from Hometown Locator]</ref> The community is adjacent to [[Interstate 76 (Colorado)|Interstate 76]].\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://geonames.usgs.gov/pls/gnispublic/f?p=gnispq:3:4533634315316859::NO::P3_FID:180807 Profile of Tampa from the USGS]\n*[http://colorado.hometownlocator.com/co/weld/tampa.cfm Tampa profile from Hometown Locator]\n\n{{Weld County, Colorado}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Unincorporated communities in Weld County, Colorado]]\n[[Category:Unincorporated communities in Colorado]]\n", "text_old": "<!-- Please do not remove or change this AfD message until the discussion has been closed. -->\n{{Article for deletion/dated|page=Tampa, Colorado|timestamp=20200328213223|year=2020|month=March|day=28|substed=yes}}\n<!-- Once discussion is closed, please place on talk page: {{Old AfD multi|page=Tampa, Colorado|date=28 March 2020|result='''keep'''}} -->\n<!-- End of AfD message, feel free to edit beyond this point -->\n{{Infobox settlement\n|name                     = Tampa\n|official_name            = \n|settlement_type          = [[Unincorporated area|Unincorporated community]]\n|nickname                 = \n|motto                    =\n\n<!-- Images -->\n|image_skyline            = \n|imagesize               